Maureen Ihua-Maduenyi The Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria and the Nigerian Copyright Commission plan to develop and implement a national anti-piracy strategy to address the sale of pirated books, films, music and other copyright infringing materials in and around the nationâ€™s local and international airports. A joint statement by the two federal agencies on Sunday explained that the Managing Director of FAAN, Capt. Rabiu Yadudu, and Director-General of the NCC, Mr John Asein, met recently at FAAN headquarters in Lagos, where the decision was taken. Both agencies said they had agreed to work out the modalities for sustained proactive enforcement to ensure that the interest of right owners was adequately protected. Copyright PUNCH.
